LoreTime is a date plugin geared towards RP servers. When a player issues the /loretime command, they are given the current in-game date and time. The days, months, and years can by configured to fit any server's theme!

CHANGELOG:
Version 1.5.0
- Updated for 1.2.4-R1.0
- Added: setcolor command!
- Added: togglehourformat command!
- Added: nextday command!
- Added: debug command!
- Added: custom time for date change
- Added: notify on date change option
- Added: "calendars"
- Changed: "set" command to "setdate"
- Removed: single world limitation
- Optimizations
- Bug Fixes (permission issues, console errors, etc)

Version 1.4.1
- Updated for RB 1.1-R6

Version 1.4.0
- Fixed time scaling issue; sunrise is now 6am and sunset is 6pm.
- New feature: ability to toggle day suffixes.
- New feature: ability to modify day suffixes.

Version 1.3.2
- Fixed time conversion issue in 12 hour format

Version 1.3.1
- updated for Bukkit RB 1337

Version 1.3.0
- added time display
- added custom string format

Version 1.2.0
- fixed other memory leak (doh!)
- added interval option in config
- added "th", "nd", etc after date numbers
- code cleanup/comments
- chat color (configurable) 
- notify players on date change
- notify on player login (optional)

Version 1.1.1
- fixed memory leak (let me know if it still persists)
- removed config save when /lt time command was issued (oops)

Version 1.1.0
- added /lt alias
- added /lt time which returns the current time

